title: Brisé Fan, 19th century
medium: celluloid sticks, pheasant feathers, celluloid guards with oval mirror
provenance: Pre-1951: Mrs. Henry Woodward Haynes; 1951: acquired by the Museum.
creditline: Gift of Mrs. Henry Woodward Haynes
description: Brisé fan. Celluloid sticks tipped with pheasant feathers. Celluloid guards, one having an oval mirror inset and one a keyhole shaped opening, into which as knob on the other end can be inserted to lock the guards together.

tombstone.epitaph: Brisé Fan, 19th century; celluloid sticks, pheasant feathers, celluloid guards with oval mirror; Gift of Mrs. Henry Woodward Haynes; 1951-106-4
